Postoperative Care for Gynecologic surgery.
1. Drinking about 8-10 glasses of water a day. Eating a balanced diet of soft and easy-to-swallow fruits, vegetables, and proteins.
2. You may climb stairs slowly and cautiously and be sure not to lift heavy objects.
3. Keep the incision clean, so you may wash it gently while in the shower but be sure to always pat it dry and not rub. 
4. wear loose fitting clothing as to not irritate the incision while itâ€™s healing.
5. If your stools are loose, eat foods high in fiber to make them firmer.